			freeVikings

			0.2 first pre-release

			03/08/2005

I. What the hell is this?

In 1993 american Sillicon & Synapse made a very nice DOS game called
Lost Vikings. FreeVikings project has been trying to make a simillar
game from scratch. For fun without stupid restrictions of commercial
software. At this time all the code is written in Ruby-it means that
it isn't very fast (actually it's rather slow), but the development is
quick and I really enjoy it.
      The package you have just unpacked is a pre-release. It means
you should expect problems. Try to solve them. You will find a lot of
bugs. Please, report them (severus@post.cz).

II. What will I need?

Ruby >= 1.8.0 (www.ruby-lang.org) and some packages for it (raa.ruby-lang.org):
- rudl >= 0.7
- log4r
- script
- rubyunit (you don't actually need it, but without it you cannot run
tests - it's only usefull for development)

